Class Storage

java.lang.Object
APlace
Storage
public class Storage extends APlace
The Storage class represents a storage facility for coal. It extends APlace, allowing it to have a location represented by x and y coordinates. In addition to location, it stores information about coal, generation and loading times, and when it will be full.

      public Storage(double x, double y, int coal, double timeToGenerate, double timeToLoad)
      Constructs a Storage instance with specified location coordinates and initial storage parameters.
      Parameters:
      x - The x-coordinate of the storage's location.
      y - The y-coordinate of the storage's location.
      coal - The initial amount of coal in storage.
      timeToGenerate - The time it takes to generate a certain amount of coal.
      timeToLoad - The time it takes to load coal onto a transport.
